                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Chargé <persName type="to">Terres</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-12-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 726.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr. Powell’s
                    No. 1874, of the 20th ultimo, in which he states that Mr. A. Lagojannis is an
                    American citizen, of Greek origin, and that he conducts a large retail business
                    in fancy articles. He adds that, under the terms of the law now being enforced,
                    no foreigners, “except in special cases,” are allowed to conduct retail
                    business.</p>
                <p>If Mr. Lagojannis’s case is one of the special cases excepted from the terms of
                    the law he may press his claim of right to do business.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
